    "As a dealer and facilitator of deals, his clientele grew to include the Berlin museum director <a href=\"/bodew\">Wilhelm Bode</a> and the British collectors Charles Butler (1822-1910), George Salting (1835-1909) and Robert Henry Benson (1850-1929).": [],
    "In 1886 Fairfax Murray, his reputation now as much a dealer and connoisseur as a portraitist, returned to London, though wife elected to remain in Italy for most of her time.": [],
    "He formed a liaison with a local woman, Blanche Richmond, fathering children by both her and his wife in 1888.": [],
    "Fairfax Murray had five more children by Richmond.": [],
    "After a period advising for Agnew's, he became a partner.": [],
    "In 1891 he cataloged the collection for the Duke of Portland, one of the few books on art he would write, along with the 1893 catalog the Roscoe collection in Liverpool.": [
